{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I think the future of this planet depends on humans,"},{"time":4000,"text":"not technology, and we already have the knowledge --"},{"time":7000,"text":"we’re kind of at the endgame with knowledge."},{"time":10000,"text":"But we’re nowhere near the endgame"},{"time":11000,"text":"when it comes to our perception."},{"time":13000,"text":"We still have one foot in the dark ages."},{"time":17000,"text":"And when you listen to some of the presentations here --"},{"time":20000,"text":"and the extraordinary range of human capability, our understandings --"},{"time":28000,"text":"and then you contrast it with the fact"},{"time":31000,"text":"we still call this planet, \"Earth:\" it’s pretty extraordinary --"},{"time":35000,"text":"we have one foot in the dark ages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"Just quickly: Aristotle, his thing was, \"It’s not flat, stupid, it’s round.\""},{"time":45000,"text":"Galileo -- he had the Inquisition, so he had to be a little bit more polite --"},{"time":50000,"text":"his was, \"It’s not in the middle, you know.\""},{"time":55000,"text":"And Hawkes: \"it’s not earth, stupid, it’s ocean.\""},{"time":60000,"text":"This is an ocean planet."},{"time":62000,"text":"T.S. Eliot really said it for me --"},{"time":64000,"text":"and this should give you goose bumps:"},{"time":66000,"text":"\"we shall not cease from exploration"},{"time":68000,"text":"and the end of our exploring shall be to return"},{"time":71000,"text":"where we started and know the place for the first time.\""},{"time":75000,"text":"And the next lines are, \"Through the unknown remembered gate,"},{"time":79000,"text":"where the last of earth discovered"},{"time":81000,"text":"is that which is the beginning.\""},{"time":85000,"text":"So I have one message."},{"time":88000,"text":"It seems to me that we’re all pointed in the wrong direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"For the rocketeers in the audience:"},{"time":96000,"text":"I love what you’re doing, I admire the guts,"},{"time":99000,"text":"I admire the courage -- but your rockets"},{"time":100000,"text":"are pointed in the wrong goddamn direction."},{"time":103000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":107000,"text":"And it’s all a question of perspective."},{"time":109000,"text":"Let me try and tell you --"},{"time":111000,"text":"I don’t mean to insult you, but look,"},{"time":114000,"text":"if I -- and I’m not doing this for real"},{"time":116000,"text":"because it would be an insult,"},{"time":117000,"text":"so I’m going to pretend, and it softens the blow --"},{"time":119000,"text":"I’m going to tell you what you’re thinking."},{"time":121000,"text":"If I held up a square that was one foot square and the color of earth,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and I held up another square that was the root two square --"},{"time":131000,"text":"so it’s 1.5 times bigger -- and was the color of the oceans;"},{"time":135000,"text":"and I said, what is the relative value of these two things?"},{"time":138000,"text":"Well, it’s the relative importance."},{"time":139000,"text":"You would say -- yeah, yeah, yeah, we all know this;"},{"time":142000,"text":"water covers twice the area of the planet than dry land."},{"time":147000,"text":"But it’s a question of perception,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and if that’s what you’re thinking,"},{"time":150000,"text":"if that’s what you think I mean when I say,"},{"time":152000,"text":"\"This is an ocean planet stupidly called 'Earth.'\""},{"time":155000,"text":"If you think that that’s the relative importance,"},{"time":158000,"text":"two to one, you’re wrong by a factor of ten."},{"time":162000,"text":"Now, you’re not as thick as two short planks,"},{"time":164000,"text":"but you sound like it when you say \"Earth,\""},{"time":167000,"text":"because that demonstration, if I turned around this way --"},{"time":172000,"text":"that earth plane would be as thin as paper."},{"time":178000,"text":"It’s a thin film, two-dimensional existence."},{"time":181000,"text":"The ocean representation would have a depth to it."},{"time":184000,"text":"And if you hefted those two things"},{"time":186000,"text":"you might find that the relative scale of those is 20 to 1."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"It turns out that something more than"},{"time":194000,"text":"94 percent of life on earth is aquatic."},{"time":198000,"text":"That means that us terrestrials occupy a minority."},{"time":203000,"text":"The problem we have in believing that"},{"time":205000,"text":"is -- you just have to give up this notion"},{"time":207000,"text":"that this Earth was created for us."},{"time":209000,"text":"Because it’s a problem we have."},{"time":211000,"text":"If this is an ocean planet"},{"time":213000,"text":"and we only have a small minority of this planet,"},{"time":217000,"text":"it just interferes with a lot of what humanity thinks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"Okay. Let me criticize this thing."},{"time":225000,"text":"I’m not talking about James Cameron --"},{"time":227000,"text":"although I could, but I won’t."},{"time":229000,"text":"You really do have to go and see his latest film,"},{"time":231000,"text":"\"Aliens of the Deep.\" It’s incredible."},{"time":234000,"text":"It features two of these deep rovers,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and I can criticize them because these sweet things are mine."},{"time":240000,"text":"This, I think, represents one of the most beautiful"},{"time":242000,"text":"classic submersibles built."},{"time":245000,"text":"If you look at that sub, you’ll see a sphere."},{"time":249000,"text":"This is an acryclic sphere."},{"time":250000,"text":"It generates all of the buoyancy,"},{"time":252000,"text":"all of the payload for the craft,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and the batteries are down here hanging underneath,"},{"time":256000,"text":"exactly like a balloon."},{"time":258000,"text":"This is the envelope, and this is the gondola, the payload."},{"time":262000,"text":"Also coming up later for criticism are these massive lights."},{"time":267000,"text":"And this one actually carries two great manipulators."},{"time":270000,"text":"It actually is a very good working sub --"},{"time":272000,"text":"that’s what it was designed for."},{"time":275000,"text":"The problem with it is --"},{"time":277000,"text":"and the reason I will never build another one like it --"},{"time":279000,"text":"is that this is a product of two-dimensional thinking."},{"time":284000,"text":"It’s what we humans do when we go in the ocean as engineers;"},{"time":287000,"text":"we take all our terrestrial hang-ups,"},{"time":290000,"text":"all our constraints -- importantly,"},{"time":292000,"text":"these two-dimensional constraints that we have,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and they’re so constrained we don’t even understand it --"},{"time":298000,"text":"and we take them underwater."},{"time":300000,"text":"You notice that Jim Cameron is sitting in a seat."},{"time":304000,"text":"A seat works in a two-dimensional world,"},{"time":306000,"text":"where gravity blasts down on that seat, OK?"},{"time":311000,"text":"And in a two-dimensional world,"},{"time":313000,"text":"we do know about the third dimension"},{"time":314000,"text":"but we don’t use it because to go up"},{"time":316000,"text":"requires an awful lot of energy against gravity."},{"time":319000,"text":"And then our mothers tell us,"},{"time":320000,"text":"\"Careful you don’t fall down\" -- because you’ll fall over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"Now, go into the real atmosphere of this planet."},{"time":329000,"text":"This planet has an inner atmosphere of water;"},{"time":333000,"text":"it’s its inner atmosphere. It has two atmospheres --"},{"time":335000,"text":"a lesser, outer gaseous atmosphere, a lighter one."},{"time":339000,"text":"Most of life on earth is in that inner atmosphere."},{"time":343000,"text":"And that life enjoys a three-dimensional existence,"},{"time":346000,"text":"which is alien to us."},{"time":349000,"text":"Fish do not sit in seats."},{"time":353000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":354000,"text":"They don’t. Their mothers don’t say to little baby fish,"},{"time":360000,"text":"\"Careful you don’t fall over.\""},{"time":362000,"text":"They don’t fall over. They don’t fall."},{"time":365000,"text":"They live in a three-dimensional world"},{"time":366000,"text":"where there is no difference in energy"},{"time":368000,"text":"between going this way, that way, that way or that way."},{"time":371000,"text":"It’s truly a three-dimensional space."},{"time":373000,"text":"And we’re only just beginning to grasp it."},{"time":375000,"text":"I don’t know of any other submersible,"},{"time":378000,"text":"or even remote, that just takes advantage"},{"time":382000,"text":"that this is a three-dimensional space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"This is the way we should be going into the oceans."},{"time":387000,"text":"This is a three-dimensional machine."},{"time":390000,"text":"What we need to do is go down into the ocean with the freedom of the animals,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and move in this three-dimensional space."},{"time":395000,"text":"OK, this is good stuff."},{"time":396000,"text":"This is man’s first attempt at flying underwater."},{"time":399000,"text":"Right now, I’m just coming down on this gorgeous, big, giant manta ray."},{"time":405000,"text":"She has twice the wingspan that I do."},{"time":408000,"text":"There I’m coming; she sees me."},{"time":410000,"text":"And just notice how she rolls under and turns;"},{"time":414000,"text":"she doesn’t sit there and try and blow air into a tank"},{"time":416000,"text":"and kind of flow up or sink down -- she just rolls."},{"time":420000,"text":"And the craft that I’m in --"},{"time":422000,"text":"this hasn’t been shown before."},{"time":424000,"text":"Chris asked us to show stuff that hasn’t been shown before."},{"time":427000,"text":"I wanted you to notice"},{"time":428000,"text":"that she actually turned to come back up."},{"time":431000,"text":"There I am; I see her coming back,"},{"time":434000,"text":"coming up underneath me."},{"time":436000,"text":"I put reverse thrust and I try and pull gently down."},{"time":439000,"text":"I’m trying to do everything very gently."},{"time":441000,"text":"We spent about three hours together and she’s beginning to trust me."},{"time":444000,"text":"And this ballet is controlled by this lady here."},{"time":448000,"text":"She gets about that close and then she pulls away."},{"time":451000,"text":"So now I try and go after her, but I’m practicing flying."},{"time":457000,"text":"This is the first flying machine. This was the first prototype."},{"time":461000,"text":"This was a fly by wire. It has wings."},{"time":466000,"text":"There’re no silly buoyancy tanks --"},{"time":468000,"text":"it’s permanently, positively buoyant."},{"time":471000,"text":"And then by moving through the water"},{"time":472000,"text":"it’s able to take that control."},{"time":474000,"text":"Now, look at that; look, it’s -- she just blew me away."},{"time":477000,"text":"She just rolled right away from underneath."},{"time":481000,"text":"Really that’s the only real dive I’ve ever made in this machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"It took 10 years to build."},{"time":490000,"text":"But this lady here taught me, hah, taught me so much."},{"time":496000,"text":"We just learned so much in three hours in the water there."},{"time":500000,"text":"I just had to go and build another machine."},{"time":502000,"text":"But look here. Instead of blowing tanks"},{"time":504000,"text":"and coming up slowly without thinking about it,"},{"time":506000,"text":"it’s a little bit of back pressure,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and that sub just comes straight back up out of the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"This is an internal Sony camera. Thank you, Sony."},{"time":517000,"text":"I don’t really look that ugly,"},{"time":519000,"text":"but the camera is so close that it’s just distorted."},{"time":522000,"text":"Now, there she goes, right overhead."},{"time":524000,"text":"This is a wide-angle camera."},{"time":525000,"text":"She’s just a few inches off the top of my head."},{"time":529000,"text":"\"Aah, ha, oh, he just crossed over the top of my head about,"},{"time":536000,"text":"oh, I don’t know, just so close.\""},{"time":541000,"text":"I come back up, not for air."},{"time":542000,"text":"\"This is an incredible encounter with a manta. I’m speechless."},{"time":548000,"text":"We’ve been just feet apart. I’m going back down now.\""},{"time":551000,"text":"Okay, can we cut that? Lights back up please."},{"time":554000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"Trying to fly and keep up with that animal --"},{"time":562000,"text":"it wasn’t the lack of maneuverability that we had."},{"time":566000,"text":"It was the fact she was going so slow."},{"time":568000,"text":"I actually designed that to move faster through the water"},{"time":572000,"text":"because I thought that was the thing"},{"time":573000,"text":"that we needed to do: to move fast and get range."},{"time":576000,"text":"But after that encounter I really did want to go back with that animal and dance."},{"time":580000,"text":"She wanted to dance."},{"time":583000,"text":"And so what we needed to do was increase the wing area"},{"time":586000,"text":"so that we just had more grip, develop higher forces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"So the sub that was outside last year -- this is the one."},{"time":593000,"text":"You see the larger wing area here."},{"time":597000,"text":"Also, clearly, it was such a powerful thing,"},{"time":599000,"text":"we wanted to try and bring other people"},{"time":600000,"text":"but we couldn't figure out how to do it."},{"time":602000,"text":"So we opened the world’s first flight school."},{"time":604000,"text":"The rational for the world’s first flight school"},{"time":607000,"text":"goes something like: when the coastguards come up to me and say --"},{"time":610000,"text":"they used to leave us alone when we were diving"},{"time":613000,"text":"these goofy little spherical things,"},{"time":615000,"text":"but when we started flying around"},{"time":616000,"text":"in underwater jet fighters they got a little nervous --"},{"time":619000,"text":"they would come up and say,"},{"time":623000,"text":"\"Do you have a license for that?\""},{"time":626000,"text":"And then I’d put my sunglasses on, the beard"},{"time":628000,"text":"that would all sprout out, and I would say,"},{"time":630000,"text":"\"I don’t need no stinking license.\""},{"time":633000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":636000,"text":"\"I write these stinking license,\" which I do."},{"time":639000,"text":"So Bob Gelfond's around here --"},{"time":641000,"text":"but somebody in the audience here has license number 20."},{"time":645000,"text":"They’re one of the first subsea aviators."},{"time":648000,"text":"So we’ve run two flight schools."},{"time":651000,"text":"Where the hell that goes, I don’t know, but it’s a lot of fun."},{"time":656000,"text":"What comes next in 30 seconds? I can’t tell you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"But the patent for underwater flight --"},{"time":664000,"text":"Karen and I, we were looking at it,"},{"time":666000,"text":"some business partners wanted us to patent it --"},{"time":668000,"text":"we weren’t sure about that."},{"time":669000,"text":"We’ve decided we’re just going to let that go."},{"time":671000,"text":"It just seems wrong to try and patent --"},{"time":674000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":675000,"text":"-- the freedom for underwater flight."},{"time":677000,"text":"So anybody who wants to copy us"},{"time":678000,"text":"and come and join us, go for it."},{"time":681000,"text":"The other thing is that we’ve got much lower costs."},{"time":686000,"text":"We developed some other technology"},{"time":687000,"text":"called spider optics, and Craig Ventner asked me"},{"time":691000,"text":"to make an announcement here this morning:"},{"time":693000,"text":"we’re going to be building a beautiful, little,"},{"time":695000,"text":"small version of this -- unmanned, super deep --"},{"time":698000,"text":"for his boat to go and get back some deep sea DNA stuff."},{"time":703000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":706000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}